<div class="box">
  <h2>Events</h2>

  <h3 id="events-launch-manager">Launch Event Manager</h3>
  <p>80,000 Hours will launch in 3rd week of Hilary term. As Launch
  Event Manager, it will be your job to make it so good that the whole of
  Oxford is talking about it. Ideally, you&#39;ll have experience of organising
  large events such as balls.  </p>
  <a href="#top">back to top</a>

  <h3 id="events-assistant-events">Assistant Events Officer</h3>
  <p>Our events will promote our ideas within Oxford as well as giving
  information and experience to people who want to pursue a high impact career.
  Your events will help build up our community and you&#39;ll play a vital role in
  the launch in Hilary term.</p>
  <a href="#top">back to top</a>

  <h3 id="events-social">Social Secretary</h3>
  <p>80,000 Hours is a community, and we like to do things as diverse as
  late-night river-swimming, early morning gym-sessions, and good old fashioned
  pub nights. As our Social Secretary, you’ll come up with events from the cosy
  to the spectacular so that all our members feel at home and people who aren’t
  yet involved can’t help but join in.</p>
  <a href="#top">back to top</a>
</div>

<div class="box">
  <h2>Community</h2>
  <h3 id="community-membership">Membership Manager</h3>
  <p>Our members are vital to our mission - without dedicating their careers to
  helping people, 80,000 Hours would have no impact at all. As our
  Membership Manager, you’ll keep all of these lovely people happy - welcoming
  them into the community, making sure they get all the advice and support they
  need, and keeping in touch with them as they go into their careers.</p>
  <a href="#top">back to top</a>

  <h3 id="community-meeters">Meeters</h3>
  <p>We like to get to know all our members individually, as a meeter you&#39;ll
  take interested people out to lunch, get to know them, their ambitions, and
  see how they can fit into our community.</p>
  <a href="#top">back to top</a>
</div>

<div class="box">
  <h2>Communications</h2>
  <h3 id="communications-officer">Communications Officer</h3>
  <p>80,000 Hours has new ideas that we want people to hear, understand,
  and act upon.  As Communications Officer you&#39;ll shape our messaging strategy
  and oversee all communications content. You&#39;ll lead a team of people working
  on website content (both written and audiovisual), market research, and
  events marketing. Ideally, you&#39;ll have experience in communications and
  marketing.</p>
  <a href="#top">back to top</a>

  <h3 id="communications-market-research">Market Research Officer</h3>
  <p>The ideas behind 80,000 Hours are novel, and we need to know what
  attracts people to us and what puts them off. As our Market Research Officer,
  you’ll do market research, talk to people, and develop ways of explaining
  ourselves to different audiences. You’ll come up with creative recruitment
  methods and put them into action with the rest of the communications team.
  </p>
  <a href="#top">back to top</a>

  <h3 id="communications-press">Press Officer</h3>
  <p>As Press Officer, you&#39;ll get high-profile positive press coverage for our
  ideas and our organisation. You&#39;ll have a flair for communications and some
  experience of the media. This is a great opportunity for anyone interested in
  working in PR and communications.</p>
  <a href="#top">back to top</a>

  <h3 id="communications-marketing">Marketing Officer</h3>
  <p>Our communications team aims to inspire people to use their careers to do good and as Marketing Officer you&#39;ll be central to this task. You&#39;ll use our ideas and market research to design practical ways of communicating our novel message and then you&#39;ll put this into practice with the communications and website teams. You&#39;ll also work with the events team to promote our events.</p>
  <a href="#top">back to top</a>

  <h3 id="communications-writer">Writers and Bloggers</h3>
  <p>You will help 80,000 Hours in one of its most important aims:
  producing high quality, useful content for its members and followers. This
  content will also be at the heart of our marketing strategy. This will be
  great experience for anyone interested in journalism.</p>
  <a href="#top">back to top</a>

  <h3 id="communications-podcast">Podcast Producer</h3>
  <p>Our podcasts will be a fount of wisdom for people who want to do good with
  their career. As Podcast Producer, you’ll turn our research and advice into
  engaging audio every month, keeping our members informed and piquing the
  interest of people who aren’t yet involved.</p>
  <a href="#top">back to top</a>

  <h3 id="communications-videographer">Videographer</h3>
  <p>We&#39;d like to record our events as well as filming interviews and making
  viral videos to spread our ideas across the world. As our videographer,
  you&#39;ll develop top-notch videos to spread ideas to a large audience.</p>
  <a href="#top">back to top</a>
</div>

<div class="box">
  <h2>Research</h2>
  <h3 id="research-manager">Manager of Careers Research</h3>
  <p>Since we’re a new organisation with new ideas, we need to develop a strong
  body of knowledge and advice to help our members do the most good in their
  careers. As our Manager of Careers Research, you&#39;ll lead a team making an
  advice guide to go on our website and your team&#39;s work will support our
  talks, podcasts, and blog posts.</p>
  <a href="#top">back to top</a>

  <h3 id="research-careers">Careers Researchers</h3>
  <p>Since we’re a new organisation with new ideas, we need to develop a strong
  body of knowledge and advice to help our members do the most good in their
  careers. As a researcher, you’ll be part of a team making an advice guide to
  go on our website and your work will support our talks, podcasts, and
  blog posts. Don’t worry if you don’t have any experience of this sort, our
  Manager of Careers Research will guide you expertly through the process as
  well as providing you with a good dose of careers advice along the way. This
  role is particularly flexible and can be performed from anywhere in the
  world.</p>
  <a href="#top">back to top</a>
</div>

